item.title: A Hong Kong Poodle tested positive for a new crown with no associated symptoms.
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: According to the news just released by Hong Kong Eastweb, the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department of the Hong Kong SAR Government said on 25 October that it received a poodle whose sample tested positive for the new coronavirus. According to the department, the poodle is from Tsuen Wan and its owner is a close contact with a confirmed case of neocrowning, so the poodle was sent to the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department for quarantine last Friday (20), and the sample taken showed positive results for neocrowning.
